trans-unit.source: The background totem assets used for ID Photos of Genshin Impact characters in this app are for representing both their life paths and their elemental powers by default. The element is represented by the color used for rendering the totem. If there's no matched lifepath available, then the totem pattern will be the elemental totem instead. The elemental totem assets used in such case are from Star Rail (excl. Geo, Dendro, and Hydro), representing the Teyvat Element of each character. Nevertheless, these totems' visibility can be toggled in UI Settings.
trans-unit.target: Ang mga background na totem asset na ginagamit para sa ID Photos ng mga karakter ng Genshin Impact sa app na ito ay para sa pagpapakita ng kanilang mga landas ng buhay at mga kapangyarihang elemental bilang default. Ang elemento ay kinakatawan ng kulay na ginamit sa pag-render ng totem. Kung walang tumutugmang lifepath, ang pattern ng totem ay magiging elemental totem. Ang mga asset ng elemental totem na ginagamit sa ganitong kaso ay mula sa Star Rail (maliban sa Geo, Dendro, at Hydro), na kumakatawan sa Teyvat Element ng bawat karakter. Gayunpaman, ang visibility ng mga totem na ito ay maaaring baguhin sa UI Settings.

trans-unit.source: SRGF v1.0, established by the UIGF committee, is an exchangeable format for gacha records of Star Rail, a game produced by Cognosphere and MiHoYo. This format is marked as a vintage format and is replaced by UIGF v4.1 and has no support of new gacha pool types introduced since January 2025. There are some excellent apps on Windows which only conforms to SRGF v1.0, hence the option here for possible compatibility needs.
trans-unit.target: Ang SRGF v1.0, na itinatag ng komite ng UIGF, ay isang maaaring palitan na format para sa mga gacha record ng Star Rail, isang laro na ginawa ng Cognosphere at MiHoYo. Ang format na ito ay minarkahan bilang isang vintage format at napalitan ng UIGF v4.1 at walang suporta sa mga bagong uri ng gacha pool na naipakilala mula noong Enero 2025. Mayroong ilang magagandang apps sa Windows na sumusunod lamang sa SRGF v1.0, kaya narito ang opsyon para sa mga posibleng pangunahing pangangailangan sa kompabilidad.

trans-unit.source: UIGF v4.1, established by the UIGF committee, is a coalescent exchangeable format for gacha records of many games produced by Cognosphere and MiHoYo.

trans-unit.source: We are not authorized to publicly state what actually happened on the server hosting official gacha records. The following descriptions are assumptions based on observations. Due to possible occasional server-side issues, the game server might return duplicated gacha entries with incorrect transaction IDs, potentially polluting the local database. If the bleaching mode is enabled, this app will use the latest fetch results as the trusted source for correct transaction IDs and remove possibly incorrect entries locally, but this could be affected by potentially polluted data from the game server. Nevertheless, once a game version deprecates, all gacha records during its operation period are likely to become static and trustworthy.
trans-unit.target: Kami ay hindi awtorisadong maghayag sa publiko kung ano ang aktuwal na nangyari sa server na nagho-host ng mga opisyal na rekord ng gacha. Ang mga sumusunod na paglalarawan ay mga palagay batay sa mga obserbasyon. Dahil sa posibleng mga paminsan-minsang isyu sa server, maaaring magbalik ang game server ng mga dobleng gacha entry na may maling transaction ID, na posibleng magdulot ng polusyon sa lokal na database. Kung naka-enable ang bleaching mode, gagamitin ng app na ito ang pinakabagong resulta ng pagkuha bilang mapagkakatiwalaang pinagmulan ng tamang transaction ID at aalisin ang mga posibleng maling entry nang lokal, ngunit maaaring maapektohan ito ng potensyal na kontaminadong data mula sa game server. Gayunpaman, kapag ang isang game version ay nag-expire, malamang na ang lahat ng gacha record mula sa operasyon nito ay magiging static at mapagkakatiwalaan.

trans-unit.source:
The confidence of the standard item hit rate is based on the number of available 5-star pulls:
• High confidence: ≥10 cases • Medium confidence: 5-9 cases • Low confidence: 3-4 cases • Insufficient data: <3 cases
Reasons for insufficient confidence: • Too few 5-star pulls • Incomplete gacha history • Recently started recording • Result is higher than theoretical bounds (50%).
Note: Even when "High confidence" comes out, the final interpretation rights still belong to miHoYo, and miHoYo also has the final interpretation rights for probability calculation methods, which override this app's calculation methods.
trans-unit.target:
Ang tiwala sa standard item hit rate ay nakabatay sa bilang ng mga available na 5-star pulls:
• Mataas na tiwala: ≥10 kaso • Katamtamang tiwala: 5-9 kaso • Mababang tiwala: 3-4 kaso • Hindi sapat na data: <3 kaso
Mga dahilan ng kulang na tiwala: • Kakaunting 5-star pulls • Hindi kumpleto ang gacha history • Kakasimula pa lang mag-record • Ang resulta ay mas mataas sa theoretical bounds (50%)
Tandaan: Kahit na lumabas ang "Mataas na tiwala", ang huling karapatan sa pagbibigay-kahulugan ay nasa miHoYo pa rin, at may huling karapatan din ang miHoYo sa mga paraan ng pagkalkula ng probability, na nagiging mas mataas sa mga paraan ng pagkalkula ng app na ito.

trans-unit.source:
This device's system version is older than OS24 (iOS 17 / macOS 14 / watchOS 10), which falls outside the current service perimeter of The Pizza Helper.
Both main developers of "Pizza Helper for Genshin" (up to v4) had to step down from development in 2024 due to their own career plans, and the development of "Pizza Helper for HSR" was also suspended. The remaining developer found it overwhelming to maintain both apps alone, hence the launch of the "Unified Pizza Engine" project to combine both apps. This resulted in "The Pizza Helper" v5 which was released in mid-November 2024.
The built-in SwiftUI frameworks in older system versions have many defects that significantly affect maintenance efficiency. Therefore, the Unified Pizza Engine chose OS24 (iOS 17 / macOS 14 / watchOS 10) as its primary development target. The Observable Macro framework introduced in this generation allows the frontend to respond more quickly and precisely to micro-scale backend data changes, instead of the old Combine-based approach that would often redraw the entire UI at once. The old technology could even cause delayed UI updates and other issues, negatively impacting both user experience and development efficiency. Additionally, OS24 introduced SwiftData, which solves CoreData's long-standing concurrency-safety issues. The entire development process of the Unified Pizza Engine leverages Swift's modern concurrency technologies.
Starting from v2.5.0, "Pizza Helper for Genshin" supported the "Spiral Abyss Top Lists" (and the related personal battle report uploading feature), which was available on OS21 (iOS 14, macOS 11, watchOS 8). After the release of Pizza Helper v5 at the end of 2024, the project, out of various concerns, implemented a "zero data collection" strategy. As a result, the Spiral Abyss Leaderboard and related personal battle report uploading features were discontinued in the summer of 2025. However, this poses an obvious data security risk for existing users who cannot upgrade to OS24: after the incoming decommission of the dedicated leaderboard server, older versions of the app on older systems may still try to upload data. If the server's IP address falls into the hands of a new owner, it could lead to uncontrollable information security risks.
To address this, the three developers reached a consensus: allow The Pizza Helper v5 to be built and executable for OS21 (iOS 14, etc.) with a limitation for systems below OS24: The Pizza Helper v5 will no longer provide any features on OS21 ~ OS23 except allowing users to export their old account data (i.e. the current saying "local profile") and draw history for import on a new device running OS24 and above.
The Pizza Helper v5 cannot risk data loss by downgrading SwiftData to CoreData, so it can no longer provide service to users on systems below OS24. As always, FOSS (Free and Open Source Software) does not mean unlimited availability or unlimited responsibility. We hope for the understanding of all affected users.
trans-unit.target:
Ang bersyon ng system ng device na ito ay mas luma kaysa OS24 (iOS 17 / macOS 14 / watchOS 10), kaya hindi ito saklaw ng kasalukuyang serbisyo ng The Pizza Helper.
Ang dalawang pangunahing developer ng "Pizza Helper para sa Genshin" (hanggang v4) ay parehong kinailangang tumigil sa pag-develop noong 2024 dahil sa kani-kanilang career plans, at ang development ng "Pizza Helper para sa HSR" ay nasuspinde rin. Ang natirang developer ay natagpuang napakabigat na panatilihin ang dalawang app nang mag-isa, kaya't napagdesisyunan niyang pagsamahin ang dalawang app sa pamamagitan ng "Unified Pizza Engine." Ito ang naging The Pizza Helper v5 na inilabas noong kalagitnaan ng Nobyembre 2024.
Maraming depekto ang built-in na SwiftUI frameworks ng mas lumang system versions na malaki ang epekto sa maintenance efficiency. Kaya't napili ng Unified Pizza Engine na gawing pangunahing development target ang OS24 (iOS 17 / macOS 14 / watchOS 10). Ang Observable Macro framework na ipinakilala sa OS24 ay nagpapabilis at nagpapahusay sa pagtugon ng frontend sa maliliit na pagbabago mula sa backend data, hindi gaya ng luma at Combine-based na approach na madalas mag-redraw ng buong UI. Maaari pang magdulot ng delayed UI updates ang lumang teknolohiya at iba pang isyu na nakakaapekto sa user experience at development. Dagdag pa rito, ang SwiftData na ipinakilala sa OS24 ay nagresolba sa matagal nang concurrency-safety issues ng CoreData. Buong proseso ng pag-develop ng Unified Pizza Engine ay gumamit ng makabagong concurrency technologies ng Swift.
Simula v2.5.0, sinusuportahan ng "Pizza Helper para sa Genshin" ang "Spiral Abyss Top Lists" (at kaugnay na upload ng personal battle report) sa OS21 (iOS 14, macOS 11, watchOS 8). Pagkatapos ilabas ang The Pizza Helper v5 sa dulo ng 2024, ipinatupad ng proyekto ang "zero data collection" dahil sa iba’t ibang dahilan. Kaya’t tinanggal ang Spiral Abyss Leaderboard at kaugnay na battle report uploading sa tag-init ng 2025. Ngunit nagdudulot ito ng panganib sa data security para sa mga hindi makapag-upgrade sa OS24: kapag na-decommission ang server para sa leaderboard, maaaring subukang mag-upload pa rin ng lumang app mula sa lumang system. Kapag napunta ang server's IP sa ibang tao, maaaring magdulot ito ng hindi makontrol na panganib sa data security.
Bilang tugon, nagkasundo ang tatlong developer na payagan ang The Pizza Helper v5 na ma-build at mag-run sa OS21 (iOS 14, atbp.) ngunit limitado sa mga system na mas mababa sa OS24: tanging export ng lumang account data at draw history lang ang papayagan para sa import sa bagong device na tumatakbo sa OS24 pataas.
Hindi maaaring i-downgrade ang SwiftData papuntang CoreData dahil sa panganib ng data loss, kaya hindi na maaaring magpatuloy magbigay-serbisyo sa mga gumagamit ng system na mas mababa sa OS24. Tulad ng dati, ang FOSS (Free and Open Source Software) ay hindi nangangahulugang walang limitasyon sa availability o responsibilidad. Sana'y maunawaan ito ng mga apektadong user.

trans-unit.source: This option is extremely helpful to let the server know that you are really using your HoYoLAB / Miyoushe account on your own devices. Individual logins per UID for each game and each game-server may let the HoYoLAB / Miyoushe account server misunderstood how many device this HoYoLAB / Miyoushe account gets logged into, leading to earlier expiration of your cookies. If profile duplication happens during this process, then the existing profile will be updated instead with new cookie, the latest device fingerprint, and the latest device ID instead.
trans-unit.target: Ang opsyon na ito ay lubos na nakakatulong upang malaman ng server na talagang ginagamit mo ang iyong HoYoLAB / Miyoushe account sa iyong sariling mga device. Ang indibidwal na pag-login kada UID para sa bawat laro at bawat game-server ay maaaring magdulot ng hindi pagkakaintindihan sa server ng HoYoLAB / Miyoushe account kung ilan ang mga device na pinasukan ng iyong HoYoLAB / Miyoushe account, na maaaring magdulot ng mas maagang pag-e-expire ng iyong cookies. Kung mangyari ang pag-duplicate ng profile sa prosesong ito, ang kasalukuyang profile ay maa-update sa halip gamit ang bagong cookie, ang pinakabagong fingerprint ng device, at ang pinakabagong ID ng device.
